I am now working in a COVID-19 unit. Severe cases go to ICU. Negatives go elsewhere. I took care of a COVID-19+ husband & wife, recently, in separate rooms. We sent the wife to ICU when her oxygen tanked but before she left she said, "I know I won't make it."

I was tested a week ago for COVID-19. My results came back today - negative. I work as a bedside RN. We have cases of COVID-19 where I work. No one knows how their body will respond. Healthy, young people can die from it. I'm at a higher risk for complications. 

I'm scared.
